# Recommendation Engine - Software Architecture
# Twitter-Inspired 7-Step Recommendation Pipeline

## ============================================================================
## 1. HIGH-LEVEL SYSTEM ARCHITECTURE
## ============================================================================

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph "Client Layer"
        API[RecommendationEngine API<br/>- recommend&#40;&#41;<br/>- record_interaction&#40;&#41;<br/>- get_statistics&#40;&#41;]
        Cache[Cache Layer<br/>TTL: 300s<br/>Dict-based]
    end
    
    subgraph "Configuration"
        Config[RecommendationConfig<br/>- candidate_pool_size: 1500<br/>- in_network_ratio: 0.4<br/>- out_network_ratio: 0.5<br/>- social_proof_ratio: 0.1<br/>- light_ranking_top_k: 500<br/>- heavy_ranking_top_k: 100<br/>- exploration_strategy<br/>- safety_threshold: 0.7]
    end
    
    subgraph "Step 1: Candidate Sourcing"
        CS[CandidateSourcing<br/>Pipeline Orchestrator<br/>~1500 candidates]
        INS[InNetworkSource<br/>40% - Following Graph<br/>Content from followed authors]
        ONS[OutOfNetworkSource<br/>50% - Discovery<br/>Interest clusters + Trending + Similar users]
        SPS[SocialProofSource<br/>10% - Social Signals<br/>Friend engagement data]
    end
    
    subgraph "Step 2: Light Ranking"
        LR[LightRanker<br/>Fast Feature Extraction<br/>Lightweight scoring<br/>Output: Top 500]
        LF[Light Features:<br/>- Content age<br/>- Engagement velocity<br/>- Author influence<br/>- User-content match]
    end
    
    subgraph "Step 3: Heavy Ranking"
        HR[HeavyRanker<br/>Precise ML-based Ranking<br/>Multi-task predictions<br/>Output: Top 100]
        MTM[MultiTaskModel<br/>Predictions:<br/>- P&#40;like&#41;<br/>- P&#40;retweet&#41;<br/>- P&#40;reply&#41;<br/>- P&#40;click&#41;<br/>- E&#40;dwell_time&#41;<br/>- P&#40;negative&#41;]
        US[UtilityScorer<br/>Weighted Utility:<br/>utility = Σ w_i * P_i]
    end
    
    subgraph "Step 4: Exploration"
        EE[ExplorationEngine<br/>Balance Explore/Exploit<br/>Strategies:<br/>- ε-greedy<br/>- UCB<br/>- Thompson Sampling]
        Stats[Content Stats Tracker<br/>- Impressions<br/>- Rewards<br/>- Success/Failure counts]
    end
    
    subgraph "Step 5: Diversity"
        DI[DiversityInjector<br/>Feed Diversity Constraints<br/>- Topic diversity<br/>- Author diversity<br/>- Content similarity check]
    end
    
    subgraph "Step 6: Safety Filtering"
        SF[SafetyFilter<br/>Multi-detector System<br/>Threshold: 0.7]
        TD[ToxicityDetector<br/>Hate speech detection]
        MD[MisinformationDetector<br/>Fake news detection]
        SD[SpamDetector<br/>Spam pattern detection]
        ND[NSFWDetector<br/>Adult content detection]
    end
    
    subgraph "Step 7: Serving"
        Response[RecommendationResponse<br/>- recommendations<br/>- latency<br/>- metadata]
    end
    
    subgraph "Observability Infrastructure"
        Logger[Logger System<br/>File-based Trace Logging<br/>Component-specific logs]
        Tracer[RequestTracer<br/>Pipeline flow tracing<br/>Request comparison]
        Analyzer[LogAnalyzer<br/>Metrics & Analysis<br/>Performance insights]
    end
    
    API -->|initialize with| Config
    API -->|check| Cache
    Cache -.->|miss| API
    
    API -->|1. Generate candidates| CS
    CS --> INS
    CS --> ONS
    CS --> SPS
    CS -->|deduplicated ~1500| LR
    
    LR --> LF
    LR -->|2. Top 500| HR
    
    HR --> MTM
    HR --> US
    HR -->|3. Top 100 with utility| EE
    
    EE <--> Stats
    EE -->|4. Exploration adjusted| DI
    
    DI -->|5. Diversified| SF
    
    SF --> TD
    SF --> MD
    SF --> SD
    SF --> ND
    SF -->|6. Safe content| Response
    
    Response -->|7. Final results| API
    API -->|cache & return| Cache
    
    API -.->|structured logging| Logger
    Logger --> Tracer
    Logger --> Analyzer
    
    style API fill:#2ecc71,stroke:#27ae60,stroke-width:4px,color:#fff
    style Config fill:#3498db,stroke:#2980b9,stroke-width:2px,color:#fff
    style CS fill:#e74c3c,stroke:#c0392b,stroke-width:2px,color:#fff
    style LR fill:#f39c12,stroke:#d68910,stroke-width:2px,color:#fff
    style HR fill:#e67e22,stroke:#d35400,stroke-width:2px,color:#fff
    style EE fill:#9b59b6,stroke:#8e44ad,stroke-width:2px,color:#fff
    style DI fill:#16a085,stroke:#138d75,stroke-width:2px,color:#fff
    style SF fill:#c0392b,stroke:#a93226,stroke-width:2px,color:#fff
    style Response fill:#2ecc71,stroke:#27ae60,stroke-width:2px,color:#fff
    style Logger fill:#34495e,stroke:#2c3e50,stroke-width:2px,color:#fff
```

## ============================================================================
## 2. DETAILED CLASS DIAGRAM WITH RELATIONSHIPS
## ============================================================================

```mermaid
classDiagram
    %% ========================================
    %% Core Engine & Response
    %% ========================================
    class RecommendationEngine {
        -config: RecommendationConfig
        -logger: Logger
        -candidate_sourcing: CandidateSourcing
        -light_ranker: LightRanker
        -heavy_ranker: HeavyRanker
        -exploration_engine: ExplorationEngine
        -diversity_injector: DiversityInjector
        -safety_filter: SafetyFilter
        -cache: Dict[str, Any]
        -request_count: int
        -total_latency: float
        +__init__(config: Optional[RecommendationConfig])
        +recommend(user_id: str, num_results: int, context: Optional[Dict]) RecommendationResponse
        +record_interaction(user_id: str, content_id: str, interaction_type: str, **kwargs) None
        +get_statistics() Dict[str, Any]
    }
    
    class RecommendationResponse {
        +recommendations: List[Any]
        +latency: float
        +metadata: Dict[str, Any]
        +__init__(recommendations, latency, metadata)
    }
    
    %% ========================================
    %% Configuration
    %% ========================================
    class RecommendationConfig {
        +candidate_pool_size: int = 1500
        +in_network_ratio: float = 0.4
        +out_network_ratio: float = 0.5
        +social_proof_ratio: float = 0.1
        +light_ranking_top_k: int = 500
        +heavy_ranking_top_k: int = 100
        +exploration_strategy: str = "epsilon_greedy"
        +epsilon: float = 0.1
        +ucb_confidence: float = 2.0
        +max_same_author: int = 2
        +max_topic_repetition: float = 0.3
        +min_topic_diversity: int = 5
        +safety_threshold: float = 0.7
        +enable_toxicity_filter: bool = True
        +enable_spam_filter: bool = True
        +cache_ttl: int = 300
        +target_latency_ms: int = 100
        +enable_ab_testing: bool = True
        +user_embedding_dim: int = 128
        +content_embedding_dim: int = 128
        +hidden_dim: int = 256
        +log_level: str = "INFO"
        +trace_dir: Path
        +to_dict() Dict[str, Any]
    }
    
    %% ========================================
    %% Candidate Sourcing Layer
    %% ========================================
    class CandidateSourcing {
        -config: RecommendationConfig
        -logger: Logger
        -in_network_source: InNetworkSource
        -out_network_source: OutOfNetworkSource
        -social_proof_source: SocialProofSource
        +__init__(config: RecommendationConfig)
        +generate_candidates(user_id: str) List~Dict~
        -_deduplicate(candidates: List~Dict~) List~Dict~
    }
    
    class InNetworkSource {
        -config: RecommendationConfig
        -logger: Logger
        -following_graph: Dict[str, List[str]]
        +__init__(config: RecommendationConfig)
        +generate_candidates(user_id: str, limit: int) List~Dict~
        -_get_following(user_id: str) List[str]
        -_get_author_content(author_id: str, limit: int) List~Dict~
    }
    
    class OutOfNetworkSource {
        -config: RecommendationConfig
        -logger: Logger
        -interest_clusters: Dict[str, List[str]]
        -trending_content: List~Dict~
        +__init__(config: RecommendationConfig)
        +generate_candidates(user_id: str, limit: int) List~Dict~
        -_get_interest_based_content(user_id: str, limit: int) List~Dict~
        -_get_trending_content(limit: int) List~Dict~
        -_get_similar_users_content(user_id: str, limit: int) List~Dict~
        -_get_user_interests(user_id: str) List[str]
    }
    
    class SocialProofSource {
        -config: RecommendationConfig
        -logger: Logger
        -friend_graph: Dict[str, List[str]]
        +__init__(config: RecommendationConfig)
        +generate_candidates(user_id: str, limit: int) List~Dict~
        -_get_friends(user_id: str) List[str]
        -_get_friend_engagements(friend_id: str, limit: int) List~Dict~
    }
    
    %% ========================================
    %% Ranking Layer
    %% ========================================
    class LightRanker {
        -config: RecommendationConfig
        -logger: Logger
        +__init__(config: RecommendationConfig)
        +rank(candidates: List~Dict~, user_id: str) List~Dict~
        -_extract_light_features(candidate: Dict, user_id: str) Dict[str, float]
        -_compute_light_score(features: Dict[str, float]) float
    }
    
    class HeavyRanker {
        -config: RecommendationConfig
        -logger: Logger
        -multi_task_model: MultiTaskModel
        -utility_scorer: UtilityScorer
        +__init__(config: RecommendationConfig)
        +rank(candidates: List~Dict~, user_id: str) List~Dict~
        -_extract_deep_features(candidate: Dict, user_id: str) Dict[str, Any]
        -_get_user_preferences(user_id: str) Dict[str, float]
    }
    
    class MultiTaskModel {
        +predict(features: Dict[str, Any]) Dict[str, float]
    }
    
    class UtilityScorer {
        +score(predictions: Dict[str, float], user_preferences: Dict[str, float]) float
    }
    
    %% ========================================
    %% Optimization Layer
    %% ========================================
    class ExplorationEngine {
        -config: RecommendationConfig
        -logger: Logger
        -content_stats: Dict[str, Dict[str, Any]]
        -total_impressions: int
        +__init__(config: RecommendationConfig)
        +apply_exploration(ranked: List~Dict~, user_id: str) List~Dict~
        -_epsilon_greedy(ranked: List~Dict~) List~Dict~
        -_ucb(ranked: List~Dict~) List~Dict~
        -_thompson_sampling(ranked: List~Dict~) List~Dict~
        +record_impression(content_id: str, engagement: bool, reward: float)
    }
    
    class DiversityInjector {
        -config: RecommendationConfig
        -logger: Logger
        +__init__(config: RecommendationConfig)
        +inject_diversity(ranked: List~Dict~) List~Dict~
        -_meets_diversity_constraints(content: Dict, topics_seen: Set, authors_seen: Dict, content_texts: List) bool
        -_is_too_similar(text: str, previous_texts: List[str]) bool
    }
    
    %% ========================================
    %% Safety & Quality Layer
    %% ========================================
    class SafetyFilter {
        -config: RecommendationConfig
        -logger: Logger
        -toxicity_detector: ToxicityDetector
        -misinfo_detector: MisinformationDetector
        -spam_detector: SpamDetector
        -nsfw_detector: NSFWDetector
        -thresholds: Dict[str, float]
        +__init__(config: RecommendationConfig)
        +filter(candidates: List~Dict~) List~Dict~
        -_assess_safety(content: Dict) float
        -_log_filtered_content(content: Dict, safety_score: float)
    }
    
    class ToxicityDetector {
        +score(text: str) float
    }
    
    class MisinformationDetector {
        +score(content: Dict) float
    }
    
    class SpamDetector {
        +score(content: Dict) float
    }
    
    class NSFWDetector {
        +score(content: Dict) float
    }
    
    %% ========================================
    %% Utilities & Infrastructure
    %% ========================================
    class Logger {
        <<utility>>
        +get_logger(name: str, component: str) logging.Logger
    }
    
    class RequestTracer {
        -analyzer: LogAnalyzer
        +__init__(trace_dir: Optional[str])
        +trace_recommendation_flow(request_id: str) Dict[str, Any]
        +print_recommendation_flow(request_id: str)
        +compare_requests(request_id1: str, request_id2: str) Dict[str, Any]
    }
    
    class LogAnalyzer {
        +trace_request(request_id: str) List
    }
    
    %% ========================================
    %% Relationships - Composition
    %% ========================================
    RecommendationEngine *-- RecommendationConfig
    RecommendationEngine *-- CandidateSourcing
    RecommendationEngine *-- LightRanker
    RecommendationEngine *-- HeavyRanker
    RecommendationEngine *-- ExplorationEngine
    RecommendationEngine *-- DiversityInjector
    RecommendationEngine *-- SafetyFilter
    RecommendationEngine ..> RecommendationResponse : creates
    RecommendationEngine ..> Logger : uses
    
    CandidateSourcing *-- InNetworkSource
    CandidateSourcing *-- OutOfNetworkSource
    CandidateSourcing *-- SocialProofSource
    CandidateSourcing --> RecommendationConfig
    CandidateSourcing ..> Logger : uses
    
    InNetworkSource --> RecommendationConfig
    InNetworkSource ..> Logger : uses
    
    OutOfNetworkSource --> RecommendationConfig
    OutOfNetworkSource ..> Logger : uses
    
    SocialProofSource --> RecommendationConfig
    SocialProofSource ..> Logger : uses
    
    LightRanker --> RecommendationConfig
    LightRanker ..> Logger : uses
    
    HeavyRanker *-- MultiTaskModel
    HeavyRanker *-- UtilityScorer
    HeavyRanker --> RecommendationConfig
    HeavyRanker ..> Logger : uses
    
    ExplorationEngine --> RecommendationConfig
    ExplorationEngine ..> Logger : uses
    
    DiversityInjector --> RecommendationConfig
    DiversityInjector ..> Logger : uses
    
    SafetyFilter *-- ToxicityDetector
    SafetyFilter *-- MisinformationDetector
    SafetyFilter *-- SpamDetector
    SafetyFilter *-- NSFWDetector
    SafetyFilter --> RecommendationConfig
    SafetyFilter ..> Logger : uses
    
    RequestTracer *-- LogAnalyzer
```

## ============================================================================
## 3. RECOMMENDATION FLOW SEQUENCE DIAGRAM
## ============================================================================

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant API as RecommendationEngine
    participant Cache
    participant Config as RecommendationConfig
    participant CS as CandidateSourcing
    participant INS as InNetworkSource
    participant ONS as OutOfNetworkSource
    participant SPS as SocialProofSource
    participant LR as LightRanker
    participant HR as HeavyRanker
    participant MTM as MultiTaskModel
    participant US as UtilityScorer
    participant EE as ExplorationEngine
    participant DI as DiversityInjector
    participant SF as SafetyFilter
    participant TD as ToxicityDetector
    participant Log as Logger
    
    User->>API: recommend(user_id="agent_001", num_results=100)
    activate API
    
    API->>Log: info("Generating recommendations")
    API->>Config: Read configuration
    Config-->>API: Config parameters
    
    API->>Cache: Check cache(user_id)
    alt Cache Hit
        Cache-->>API: Cached recommendations
        API-->>User: RecommendationResponse (cached=True)
    else Cache Miss
        Cache-->>API: None
        
        Note over API,SPS: STEP 1: CANDIDATE SOURCING (~1500 candidates)
        API->>CS: generate_candidates(user_id)
        activate CS
        
        par Parallel Candidate Generation
            CS->>INS: generate_candidates(user_id, 600)
            activate INS
            Note right of INS: 40% In-Network<br/>Following graph
            INS->>INS: _get_following(user_id)
            INS->>INS: _get_author_content()
            INS-->>CS: 600 in-network candidates
            deactivate INS
        and
            CS->>ONS: generate_candidates(user_id, 750)
            activate ONS
            Note right of ONS: 50% Out-of-Network<br/>Interest + Trending + Similar
            ONS->>ONS: _get_interest_based_content()
            ONS->>ONS: _get_trending_content()
            ONS->>ONS: _get_similar_users_content()
            ONS-->>CS: 750 out-network candidates
            deactivate ONS
        and
            CS->>SPS: generate_candidates(user_id, 150)
            activate SPS
            Note right of SPS: 10% Social Proof<br/>Friend engagement
            SPS->>SPS: _get_friends(user_id)
            SPS->>SPS: _get_friend_engagements()
            SPS-->>CS: 150 social proof candidates
            deactivate SPS
        end
        
        CS->>CS: _deduplicate(all_candidates)
        CS->>Log: info("Candidates generated", count=1500)
        CS-->>API: 1500 deduplicated candidates
        deactivate CS
        
        Note over API,LR: STEP 2: LIGHT RANKING (Top 500)
        API->>LR: rank(candidates, user_id)
        activate LR
        loop For each candidate
            LR->>LR: _extract_light_features(candidate, user_id)
            Note right of LR: Features:<br/>- Content age<br/>- Engagement velocity<br/>- Author influence<br/>- User match
            LR->>LR: _compute_light_score(features)
        end
        LR->>LR: Sort by light_score
        LR->>Log: debug("Light ranking complete", count=500)
        LR-->>API: Top 500 light-ranked candidates
        deactivate LR
        
        Note over API,HR: STEP 3: HEAVY RANKING (Top 100)
        API->>HR: rank(candidates, user_id)
        activate HR
        HR->>HR: _get_user_preferences(user_id)
        loop For each candidate
            HR->>HR: _extract_deep_features(candidate, user_id)
            Note right of HR: Deep features:<br/>- User embeddings<br/>- Content embeddings<br/>- Topic match
            HR->>MTM: predict(features)
            activate MTM
            MTM->>MTM: Multi-task neural network
            MTM-->>HR: {p_like, p_retweet, p_reply, p_click, dwell_time, p_negative}
            deactivate MTM
            HR->>US: score(predictions, user_preferences)
            activate US
            US->>US: utility = Σ(w_i * P_i)
            US-->>HR: utility_score
            deactivate US
        end
        HR->>HR: Sort by utility
        HR->>Log: debug("Heavy ranking complete", count=100)
        HR-->>API: Top 100 utility-ranked candidates
        deactivate HR
        
        Note over API,EE: STEP 4: EXPLORATION
        API->>EE: apply_exploration(ranked, user_id)
        activate EE
        alt Strategy: epsilon_greedy
            EE->>EE: _epsilon_greedy(ranked)
            Note right of EE: Random exploration<br/>with probability ε=0.1
        else Strategy: ucb
            EE->>EE: _ucb(ranked)
            Note right of EE: Upper Confidence Bound<br/>UCB = mean + bonus
        else Strategy: thompson_sampling
            EE->>EE: _thompson_sampling(ranked)
            Note right of EE: Bayesian sampling<br/>Beta distribution
        end
        EE->>EE: Re-sort by adjusted utility
        EE->>Log: debug("Exploration applied", strategy)
        EE-->>API: Exploration-adjusted candidates
        deactivate EE
        
        Note over API,DI: STEP 5: DIVERSITY INJECTION
        API->>DI: inject_diversity(explored)
        activate DI
        DI->>DI: Initialize tracking (topics_seen, authors_seen)
        loop For each candidate
            DI->>DI: _meets_diversity_constraints(content, topics, authors)
            Note right of DI: Check:<br/>- Topic diversity<br/>- Author diversity<br/>- Content similarity
            alt Meets constraints
                DI->>DI: Add to diversified list
                DI->>DI: Update tracking
            else Violates constraints
                DI->>DI: Skip candidate
            end
        end
        DI->>Log: debug("Diversity injected", unique_topics, unique_authors)
        DI-->>API: Diversified candidates
        deactivate DI
        
        Note over API,SF: STEP 6: SAFETY FILTERING
        API->>SF: filter(diversified)
        activate SF
        loop For each candidate
            SF->>TD: score(text)
            TD-->>SF: toxicity_score
            SF->>SF: Check misinformation
            SF->>SF: Check spam
            SF->>SF: Check NSFW
            SF->>SF: _assess_safety(content)
            Note right of SF: safety = 1.0 * Π(1 - score_i)
            alt safety >= threshold (0.7)
                SF->>SF: Keep candidate
            else safety < threshold
                SF->>Log: warning("Content filtered", content_id, safety_score)
                SF->>SF: Remove candidate
            end
        end
        SF->>Log: info("Safety filtering complete", removed_count)
        SF-->>API: Safe, filtered candidates
        deactivate SF
        
        Note over API,User: STEP 7: SERVING & RESPONSE
        API->>API: Trim to num_results (100)
        API->>API: Calculate latency
        API->>API: Build metadata
        API->>Cache: Set cache(user_id, results, ttl=300)
        API->>Log: info("Recommendations generated", count, latency_ms)
        API-->>User: RecommendationResponse(recommendations, latency, metadata)
    end
    deactivate API
```

## ============================================================================
## 4. DATA FLOW & TRANSFORMATION PIPELINE
## ============================================================================

```mermaid
flowchart TD
    subgraph Input["Input Layer"]
        USER[User ID: agent_001]
        NUM[Num Results: 100]
        CTX[Context: device, time, location]
    end
    
    subgraph Sources["Candidate Sources"]
        direction TB
        IN[In-Network Source<br/>Following Graph<br/>40% ≈ 600 candidates]
        OUT[Out-of-Network Source<br/>Interest: 60%<br/>Trending: 30%<br/>Similar: 10%<br/>50% ≈ 750 candidates]
        SOC[Social Proof Source<br/>Friend Engagement<br/>10% ≈ 150 candidates]
    end
    
    subgraph Pool["Candidate Pool"]
        MERGE[Merge & Deduplicate<br/>~1500 unique candidates]
    end
    
    subgraph Light["Light Ranking Features"]
        direction TB
        AGE[Content Age<br/>age_score = 1 - hours/48]
        VEL[Engagement Velocity<br/>velocity_score = engagements/1000]
        INF[Author Influence<br/>influence_score = followers/100000]
        MAT[User-Content Match<br/>match_score from history]
    end
    
    subgraph LScore["Light Scoring"]
        LS[Light Score<br/>= 0.2*age + 0.3*velocity<br/>+ 0.2*influence + 0.3*match<br/>Sort & Select Top 500]
    end
    
    subgraph Deep["Heavy Ranking Features"]
        direction TB
        UE[User Embedding<br/>128-dim vector]
        CE[Content Embedding<br/>128-dim vector]
        DF[Deep Features<br/>engagement, age, topics]
    end
    
    subgraph Multi["Multi-Task Predictions"]
        direction TB
        PRED[Neural Network Predictions:<br/>P&#40;like&#41; P&#40;retweet&#41; P&#40;reply&#41;<br/>P&#40;click&#41; E&#40;dwell_time&#41;<br/>P&#40;negative_feedback&#41;]
    end
    
    subgraph Util["Utility Computation"]
        UT[Utility Score<br/>= w_like*P&#40;like&#41; + w_rt*P&#40;retweet&#41;<br/>+ w_reply*P&#40;reply&#41; + w_click*P&#40;click&#41;<br/>+ w_dwell*E&#40;dwell&#41; - w_neg*P&#40;neg&#41;<br/>Sort & Select Top 100]
    end
    
    subgraph Explore["Exploration Strategies"]
        direction TB
        EPS[ε-greedy: Random boost with P=ε]
        UCB[UCB: mean + √&#40;2*ln&#40;N&#41;/n&#41;]
        TS[Thompson: Beta&#40;α,β&#41; sampling]
    end
    
    subgraph Diverse["Diversity Constraints"]
        direction TB
        TOP[Topic Diversity<br/>max_topic_repetition: 0.3]
        AUTH[Author Diversity<br/>max_same_author: 2]
        SIM[Content Similarity<br/>Jaccard threshold: 0.7]
    end
    
    subgraph Safety["Safety Detectors"]
        direction TB
        TOX[Toxicity Detector<br/>threshold: 0.7]
        MIS[Misinformation Detector<br/>threshold: 0.7]
        SPA[Spam Detector<br/>threshold: 0.7]
        NSW[NSFW Detector<br/>threshold: 0.8]
    end
    
    subgraph Final["Final Assembly"]
        SAFE[Safety Score<br/>= 1.0 * Π&#40;1-score_i&#41;<br/>Keep if score ≥ 0.7]
        TRIM[Trim to num_results]
    end
    
    subgraph Output["Output Layer"]
        direction TB
        REC[Recommendations List<br/>Top N ranked items]
        LAT[Latency Metrics<br/>Pipeline timing]
        META[Metadata<br/>candidate_count<br/>filtered_count<br/>pipeline_steps]
    end
    
    USER --> IN
    USER --> OUT
    USER --> SOC
    
    IN --> MERGE
    OUT --> MERGE
    SOC --> MERGE
    
    MERGE --> AGE
    MERGE --> VEL
    MERGE --> INF
    MERGE --> MAT
    
    AGE --> LS
    VEL --> LS
    INF --> LS
    MAT --> LS
    
    LS --> UE
    LS --> CE
    LS --> DF
    
    UE --> PRED
    CE --> PRED
    DF --> PRED
    
    PRED --> UT
    
    UT --> EPS
    UT --> UCB
    UT --> TS
    
    EPS --> TOP
    UCB --> TOP
    TS --> TOP
    
    TOP --> AUTH
    AUTH --> SIM
    
    SIM --> TOX
    TOX --> MIS
    MIS --> SPA
    SPA --> NSW
    
    NSW --> SAFE
    SAFE --> TRIM
    
    TRIM --> REC
    TRIM --> LAT
    TRIM --> META
    
    REC --> Output
    LAT --> Output
    META --> Output
    
    style USER fill:#3498db,color:#fff
    style MERGE fill:#e74c3c,color:#fff
    style LS fill:#f39c12,color:#fff
